pulation and Spectral\nSynthesis (BPASS) models for the Red Supergiants with solar abundance, we\nderived an age of 10.7$\\pm$1 Myr, in excellent agreement with recent work by\nBeasor & Davies (10.4$^{+1.3}_{-1.2}$ Myr) based on MIST evolutionary models.\nIn Paper II, the age of W36B was reported to be 6.4$\\pm$0.5 Myr, supporting\nrecent claims of a temporal spread of several Myrs for the star-forming process\nwithin Wd 1 instead of a single monolithic starburst episode scenario.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 Apr 2022 12:06:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 19 Aug 2022 03:34:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-21"}
